    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - ADJUSTMENTS - STRIKER PIN</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601804" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>STRIKER PIN</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Door striker pin mount provides for door adjustment at enlarged hole and tapped block in
                door latch pillar. Loosen striker pin (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601897">Item 2, Figure 97</hotlnk>) to move pin up or down and forward or rearward as
                required.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1601897" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1601897" filename="../figg16/G1601897.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 97. Door Striker Pin</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. DOOR LATCH PILLAR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DOOR STRIKER PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>3. TORX HEAD TOOL</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SPACER SHIM</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use spacer shim (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601897">Item 4, Figure 97</hotlnk>) between striker pin (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601897">Item 2, Figure 97</hotlnk>) and door latch pillar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601897">Item 1, Figure 97</hotlnk>) for in or out adjustment.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After adjustment, tighten striker pin (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601897">Item 2, Figure 97</hotlnk>) to 34 to 50 ft-lbs. (46 to 68 Nm). Door should
                contact door opening weatherseal all around with slight pressure without damaging seal. Door should
                latch, lock and release without undue effort, and door should be rattle-free when vehicle is in motion.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
